<div id="outline-container-org912c8ef" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="org912c8ef">12-jan, course: NLP,  overview and the main tasks</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-org912c8ef">
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>For the linguistic part you can refer to <a href="https://faculty.washington.edu/ebender/100things-sem_prag.html">https://faculty.washington.edu/ebender/100things-sem_prag.html</a></li>
<li>For the NLP basics: <a href="https://web.stanford.edu/~jurafsky/slp3/">https://web.stanford.edu/~jurafsky/slp3/</a></li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-org9a3185c" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="org9a3185c">19-jan, course: Text classification</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-org9a3185c">
<p>
Further and essential readings: 
</p>
<ul class="org-ul">
<li><a href="http://www.jmlr.org/papers/volume12/collobert11a/collobert11a.pdf">Natural Language Processing (Almost) from Scratch</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.jmlr.org/papers/volume3/bengio03a/bengio03a.pdf">A Neural Probabilistic Language Model</a></li>
<li><a href="http://u.cs.biu.ac.il/~yogo/nnlp.pdf">A Primer on Neural Network Models for Natural Language Processing</a></li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

